Note: Memory Statistics
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "get_page_size" returns Integer:
    Note: Standard page size on x86_64 Linux
    Return 4096
End Process

Process called "get_cache_line_size" returns Integer:
    Note: Typical L1 cache line size
    Return 64
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: C-RUNTIME COMPATIBILITY ALIASES
Note: ============================================================================
Note: The legacy v0.0.8.4.5.3.5 C runtime exported `memory_free(ptr)` as a
Note: libc free()-style wrapper. The canonical name in the Runa runtime is
Note: deallocate (defined above with full registry tracking, generation
Note: counters, and tier-aware behavior). This alias forwards so code that
Note: still spells the C name resolves at link time.

Process called "memory_free" takes ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc deallocate with ptr
End Process
